# 🚀 Code Playground (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)

🔴 Live Demo: https://nithin-01-reddy.github.io/code-playground/
📂 GitHub Repository: https://github.com/NITHIN-01-Reddy/code-playground.git

A **modern in-browser code playground** that lets users write and execute **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript** in real time with live preview, templates, console output, export, and share functionality — built using **pure vanilla web technologies**.

This project is ideal for **frontend practice**, **college mini-projects**, and **internship-ready portfolios**.

---

## ✨ Features

* 🧩 Separate editors for **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript**
* ⚡ Live preview using sandboxed iframe (`srcdoc`)
* 🖥️ Built-in **console output panel** (log, warn, error)
* 🧠 Auto-run code on typing (debounced)
* 📦 Pre-built templates:

  * Blank Starter
  * Gradient Card
  * Particle Effect (Canvas)
  * Todo App
* 🔗 Share playground via encoded URL
* ⬇️ Export code as a single HTML file
* 🎨 Clean, modern dark UI
* 🔒 Secure execution using iframe sandboxing

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* **HTML5** – Application structure
* **CSS3** – Responsive UI & theming
* **JavaScript (ES6)** – Editor logic, preview rendering, templates, console capture

*No frameworks. No libraries. 100% Vanilla JS.*

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
code-playground/
│
├── index.html      # Main UI layout
├── styles.css      # Styling and layout
├── script.js       # Core logic (editors, preview, templates)
└── README.md       # Documentation
```

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

1. User writes code in the HTML, CSS, or JavaScript editor
2. Code is injected into a **sandboxed iframe** using `srcdoc`
3. JavaScript execution is wrapped to:

   * Capture `console.log`, `console.warn`, `console.error`
   * Send logs to parent window using `postMessage`
4. Output and logs update instantly without reloading the page

---

## ▶️ Run Locally

No installation required.

1. Download or clone the repository
2. Open `index.html` in any modern browser
3. Start coding 🚀

---

## 🔗 Share Feature

* Clicking **Share** generates a URL with encoded HTML/CSS/JS
* Anyone opening the link sees the same code loaded automatically

---

## ⬇️ Export Feature

* Clicking **Export** downloads a standalone `.html` file
* The file contains your HTML, CSS, and JS bundled together

---

## 📌 Use Cases

* Frontend practice (HTML/CSS/JS)
* Teaching & demos
* College mini / UI project
* Internship & portfolio project
* Understanding iframe sandboxing & DOM isolation

---

## 🚧 Limitations

* No backend support
* No authentication
* No persistent storage (localStorage can be added)

---

## 🌱 Future Enhancements

* 💾 Save projects using LocalStorage
* 🌙 Dark / Light mode toggle
* 🧠 AI-powered code suggestions
* 📤 Share using short links
* 🗂️ Multiple file support

